1
00:01:25,710 --> 00:01:35,020
[LIVE UP TO YOUR YOUTH]

2
00:01:35,330 --> 00:01:37,910
[Episode 18]

3
00:01:38,200 --> 00:01:40,450
So what did you figure out?

4
00:01:41,150 --> 00:01:43,570
It turns out
that my dad's roommates include

5
00:01:43,570 --> 00:01:45,890
a singer, a musician,

6
00:01:46,070 --> 00:01:47,130
a big star,

7
00:01:47,570 --> 00:01:49,729
a great scriptwriter for movies,

8
00:01:49,810 --> 00:01:50,940
and a great painter.

9
00:01:52,039 --> 00:01:53,789
There are so many people doing big things.

10
00:01:53,789 --> 00:01:56,920
I've never seen any
in the county or the village.

11
00:01:54,970 --> 00:02:02,480
[Endeavor]

12
00:01:57,710 --> 00:01:59,850
Dad, I understand now.

13
00:02:00,420 --> 00:02:02,480
This is the real grandeur of Beijing.

14
00:02:03,710 --> 00:02:05,810
That's my boy! Well said!

15
00:02:12,360 --> 00:02:12,860
Dad.

16
00:02:13,240 --> 00:02:15,030
Today, I want everyone here

17
00:02:15,240 --> 00:02:16,360
to be my witnesses.

18
00:02:16,840 --> 00:02:18,690
I will go back and study hard.

19
00:02:19,090 --> 00:02:20,430
When I take the college entrance exam,

20
00:02:20,430 --> 00:02:22,030
I'll definitely
get into a university in Beijing.

21
00:02:22,030 --> 00:02:23,970
Great, we'll wait for you in Beijing.

22
00:02:23,970 --> 00:02:25,829
We'll all wait for you in Beijing.

23
00:02:26,180 --> 00:02:27,630
Come, cheers.

24
00:02:29,960 --> 00:02:31,050
Come on, come on.

25
00:02:31,130 --> 00:02:32,250
Sit down.

26
00:02:32,310 --> 00:02:33,090
Hurry and take a seat.

27
00:02:33,090 --> 00:02:34,400
We've been waiting for you for ages!

28
00:02:34,400 --> 00:02:35,079
Pour the wine.

29
00:02:35,079 --> 00:02:36,680
It's freezing cold outside.

30
00:02:38,680 --> 00:02:39,250
When did you leave?

31
00:02:39,250 --> 00:02:41,050
Come on, let me scratch his back.

32
00:02:41,190 --> 00:02:42,079
Cold! Cold!

33
00:02:42,650 --> 00:02:43,380
It's so cold.

34
00:02:43,870 --> 00:02:45,130
I'm freezing!

35
00:02:45,180 --> 00:02:47,110
Come on, eat up. Take a seat and eat.

36
00:02:47,310 --> 00:02:47,810
Come on.

37
00:02:49,130 --> 00:02:50,150
That's good.

38
00:02:51,010 --> 00:02:52,140
Mr. Guo, Mrs. Jiang,

39
00:02:52,750 --> 00:02:53,930
I just

40
00:02:53,960 --> 00:02:55,370
tidied up a vacant room for you.

41
00:02:55,370 --> 00:02:57,020
Before the Spring Festival,
your family of three

42
00:02:57,020 --> 00:02:58,440
can stay at the Seasons Change Hostel.

43
00:02:58,440 --> 00:02:59,170
Is that okay?

44
00:03:00,020 --> 00:03:01,460
Over there, we...

45
00:03:01,520 --> 00:03:02,590
-Nice!
-Good!

46
00:03:02,630 --> 00:03:03,930
-It's good.
-Brilliant.

47
00:03:03,930 --> 00:03:04,560
From now on,

48
00:03:04,560 --> 00:03:05,580
we can enjoy
Mrs. Jiang's cooking every day!

49
00:03:05,580 --> 00:03:06,370
-Right?
-Yeah.

50
00:03:06,370 --> 00:03:07,170
Amazing food.

51
00:03:08,460 --> 00:03:10,040
Mrs. Jiang says thank you.

52
00:03:10,080 --> 00:03:11,420
Come on, just eat up.

53
00:03:11,530 --> 00:03:13,130
We've been talking too much.

54
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:28,290
[Seasons Change Hostel]

55
00:03:34,310 --> 00:03:34,900
Ranran,

56
00:03:36,430 --> 00:03:37,829
can I go in and take a look?

57
00:03:38,130 --> 00:03:39,530
It's quite messy inside.

58
00:03:47,910 --> 00:03:49,170
Actually, I just want

59
00:03:49,200 --> 00:03:50,800
to reminisce about my youth.

60
00:03:58,990 --> 00:04:03,440
[Seasons Change Hostel]

61
00:04:10,410 --> 00:04:11,190
Back then,

62
00:04:11,410 --> 00:04:13,710
I also lived
in this kind of hutong in Beijing.

63
00:04:13,710 --> 00:04:14,870
I remember the landlord

64
00:04:14,870 --> 00:04:15,470
renovated

65
00:04:15,470 --> 00:04:16,750
a very small room,

66
00:04:17,180 --> 00:04:18,440
with only a mat inside,

67
00:04:19,329 --> 00:04:20,329
and no furniture.

68
00:04:20,329 --> 00:04:21,190
My daily necessities,

69
00:04:21,190 --> 00:04:22,220
pots, and pans were

70
00:04:22,220 --> 00:04:23,550
all placed on the floor.

71
00:04:24,240 --> 00:04:25,040
In winter,

72
00:04:25,310 --> 00:04:27,130
it was so cold
that I didn't even dare get out of bed.

73
00:04:27,130 --> 00:04:28,930
In summer, it was scorching hot.

74
00:04:29,180 --> 00:04:30,510
Which way should we go?

75
00:04:31,010 --> 00:04:31,650
That way.

76
00:04:52,010 --> 00:04:53,180
I got up in the morning,

77
00:04:53,180 --> 00:04:54,210
had breakfast,

78
00:04:54,510 --> 00:04:55,500
and dressed myself up

79
00:04:55,500 --> 00:04:56,430
to look sharp...

80
00:04:56,750 --> 00:04:57,950
Ranran, you're back.

81
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:02,730
Then I combed my hair really nicely

82
00:05:02,830 --> 00:05:04,450
and went out to talk business.

83
00:05:04,450 --> 00:05:05,620
Guess what?

84
00:05:06,040 --> 00:05:06,800
After hours of talking,

85
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:08,660
I didn't even close a single deal.

86
00:05:11,270 --> 00:05:12,860
Mr. Chu, so you...

87
00:05:14,540 --> 00:05:15,400
Used to be poor?

88
00:05:16,740 --> 00:05:18,100
Who's never been poor?

89
00:05:19,360 --> 00:05:21,160
But poor as I was, I had ambition.

90
00:05:21,420 --> 00:05:23,050
At that time, I swore to myself

91
00:05:23,050 --> 00:05:23,810
that one day

92
00:05:23,810 --> 00:05:24,870
I would make big bucks,

93
00:05:24,870 --> 00:05:25,930
drive a luxury car,

94
00:05:26,270 --> 00:05:27,200
use a cell phone,

95
00:05:27,600 --> 00:05:29,060
and stay in luxury hotels.

96
00:05:29,310 --> 00:05:29,910
Of course,

97
00:05:30,240 --> 00:05:32,240
none of these is a big deal now.

98
00:05:30,570 --> 00:05:34,710
[Seasons Change Hostel]

99
00:05:34,780 --> 00:05:36,390
You are going back
to Huzhou for the New Year.

100
00:05:36,390 --> 00:05:37,990
Have you bought your ticket?

101
00:05:38,010 --> 00:05:38,630
Yes.

102
00:05:40,250 --> 00:05:41,780
Do you need any help from me?

103
00:05:43,659 --> 00:05:44,080
Okay.

104
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:48,310
Now that you know

105
00:05:48,460 --> 00:05:50,260
I recommended you for this role,

106
00:05:50,630 --> 00:05:51,890
will you still play it?

107
00:05:57,190 --> 00:05:57,659
I will.

108
00:05:59,450 --> 00:06:00,930
I want to prove myself

109
00:06:00,950 --> 00:06:02,130
and prove that you introduced them

110
00:06:02,130 --> 00:06:02,960
to a good actress,

111
00:06:02,960 --> 00:06:03,750
not a fool

112
00:06:03,750 --> 00:06:04,830
who can't act.

113
00:06:05,430 --> 00:06:06,810
I want them to thank you,

114
00:06:07,250 --> 00:06:08,850
so you don't owe them a favor.

115
00:06:10,070 --> 00:06:10,540
Good.

116
00:06:11,340 --> 00:06:12,070
I'll look forward

117
00:06:12,070 --> 00:06:13,740
to your wonderful performance,

118
00:06:13,740 --> 00:06:14,770
so they'll all come

119
00:06:14,770 --> 00:06:16,830
to thank me with sincerity one by one.

120
00:06:22,630 --> 00:06:23,770
I won't walk you inside,

121
00:06:23,770 --> 00:06:25,170
lest I cause you trouble.

122
00:06:29,130 --> 00:06:29,660
Bye-bye.

123
00:06:30,740 --> 00:06:31,270
Goodbye.

124
00:07:04,820 --> 00:07:07,290
[Seasons Change Hostel]

125
00:07:29,930 --> 00:07:39,100
[Seasons Change Hostel]

126
00:07:50,340 --> 00:07:52,159
Why are you zoning out?

127
00:07:53,070 --> 00:07:55,060
Zhang's wife was asking me

128
00:07:55,220 --> 00:07:56,659
if you had finished repairing

129
00:07:56,659 --> 00:07:57,310
Zhang's watch.

130
00:07:57,310 --> 00:07:58,890
They need it for the New Year.

131
00:07:58,890 --> 00:07:59,770
I'm fixing it.

132
00:08:00,810 --> 00:08:01,600
Come on.

133
00:08:06,490 --> 00:08:08,020
What date is New Year's Eve?

134
00:08:08,570 --> 00:08:09,220
No idea.

135
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:15,600
I'm wondering...

136
00:08:16,780 --> 00:08:17,740
Did we

137
00:08:18,660 --> 00:08:20,550
forget something?

138
00:08:21,950 --> 00:08:22,750
I have no idea.

139
00:08:23,430 --> 00:08:24,430
You figure it out.

140
00:08:26,610 --> 00:08:28,870
Maybe it's the recent temperature drop?

141
00:08:29,920 --> 00:08:31,180
Why does it feel

142
00:08:31,180 --> 00:08:33,500
so cold and so empty

143
00:08:34,150 --> 00:08:35,380
in our house?

144
00:08:36,970 --> 00:08:39,000
What's wrong with you a-again?

145
00:08:39,010 --> 00:08:39,740
Why are you laughing?

146
00:08:39,740 --> 00:08:40,770
No, I mean,

147
00:08:40,860 --> 00:08:41,750
just look at you.

148
00:08:41,750 --> 00:08:43,890
Look at your habit of not being honest
with what you really want.

149
00:08:43,890 --> 00:08:45,510
If you want to call your son

150
00:08:45,510 --> 00:08:47,170
to ask him when he's buying the ticket

151
00:08:47,170 --> 00:08:48,200
and if he's coming back for the New Year,

152
00:08:48,200 --> 00:08:49,740
just go make a call.

153
00:08:49,760 --> 00:08:51,600
You're the one missing your son,

154
00:08:51,650 --> 00:08:53,150
and you're dragging me into it.

155
00:08:53,150 --> 00:08:54,600
You go ahead and call him.

156
00:08:54,620 --> 00:08:55,460
Call him if you want.

157
00:08:55,460 --> 00:08:56,860
Why make it sound like I...

158
00:08:56,860 --> 00:08:58,520
Did I provoke you? Spare me...

159
00:08:58,600 --> 00:09:01,730
Yeah, yeah, I'm missing him
and going to call him. Man...

160
00:09:02,060 --> 00:09:03,920
No need to look for the phone book.

161
00:09:04,130 --> 00:09:05,300
Just dial directly.

162
00:09:05,320 --> 00:09:06,220
010.

163
00:09:07,260 --> 00:09:10,310
6235 522

164
00:09:16,910 --> 00:09:17,910
Northeasterner?

165
00:09:18,920 --> 00:09:20,720
This is Shengli's mom speaking.

166
00:09:20,910 --> 00:09:21,870
Yes.

167
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:23,250
Happy New Year!

168
00:09:31,870 --> 00:09:32,670
Pair of fours.

169
00:09:33,750 --> 00:09:35,550
Where are Xiaobao and your wife?

170
00:09:35,650 --> 00:09:36,710
They went shopping

171
00:09:37,290 --> 00:09:39,100
to buy stuff for the family.

172
00:09:39,120 --> 00:09:41,010
Liangliang kept me here

173
00:09:41,320 --> 00:09:42,150
to play cards with him.

174
00:09:42,150 --> 00:09:44,080
Xu Shengli, there's a call for you.

175
00:09:46,400 --> 00:09:47,730
Your mom's on the phone.

176
00:09:48,980 --> 00:09:49,610
Hands off.

177
00:09:49,820 --> 00:09:52,420
You tried to peek at his cards
as soon as he left?

178
00:09:53,250 --> 00:09:54,310
-Your turn.
-Guys.

179
00:09:54,790 --> 00:09:56,190
It's almost the New Year.

180
00:09:56,750 --> 00:09:57,600
When are you leaving?

181
00:09:57,600 --> 00:09:58,320
Come with me to register,

182
00:09:58,320 --> 00:09:59,580
so I can wrap up my work.

183
00:10:00,390 --> 00:10:01,320
Whose turn is it?

184
00:10:01,530 --> 00:10:02,090
My turn.

185
00:10:02,250 --> 00:10:03,020
Pair of tens.

186
00:10:03,860 --> 00:10:05,500
Clear. Pair of jacks.

187
00:10:06,390 --> 00:10:07,220
I'll register the 28th

188
00:10:07,220 --> 00:10:08,870
of the New Year's first month.

189
00:10:08,870 --> 00:10:09,620
Our family of three

190
00:10:09,620 --> 00:10:11,770
will stay and have fun in Beijing
for a few more days.

191
00:10:11,770 --> 00:10:13,370
Pair of jacks. Pair of jacks.

192
00:10:13,370 --> 00:10:14,460
Register mine, too.

193
00:10:14,460 --> 00:10:15,410
I'm leaving a day earlier than Zongbao.

194
00:10:15,410 --> 00:10:16,080
The 27th.

195
00:10:16,200 --> 00:10:17,060
Pair of queens.

196
00:10:18,120 --> 00:10:18,980
What about you?

197
00:10:21,080 --> 00:10:21,930
I'm asking you.

198
00:10:21,930 --> 00:10:22,810
Play.

199
00:10:22,940 --> 00:10:23,360
You...

200
00:10:24,370 --> 00:10:25,770
If you don't play, I will.

201
00:10:27,110 --> 00:10:28,910
Pair of twos, and a little joker.

202
00:10:29,850 --> 00:10:30,660
Stick it on.

203
00:10:32,260 --> 00:10:34,540
Why are you the only one
getting these stuck on?

204
00:10:34,540 --> 00:10:36,000
Come on, you stay. Come on.

205
00:10:36,320 --> 00:10:37,180
One more round.

206
00:10:43,040 --> 00:10:43,830
Hello, Mom.

207
00:10:44,690 --> 00:10:45,560
Shengli,

208
00:10:46,390 --> 00:10:48,670
well, are you doing okay?

209
00:10:48,670 --> 00:10:49,550
I'm doing pretty well.

210
00:10:49,550 --> 00:10:50,670
I just want to know

211
00:10:50,790 --> 00:10:53,240
if you've bought your ticket
for the Spring Festival.

212
00:10:53,240 --> 00:10:54,080
Around the Spring Festival,

213
00:10:54,080 --> 00:10:56,080
tickets are hard to get nationwide.

214
00:10:56,080 --> 00:10:57,460
Mom, just rest assured.

215
00:10:57,460 --> 00:10:59,190
I already bought it in advance.

216
00:11:00,620 --> 00:11:01,250
Great!

217
00:11:01,250 --> 00:11:02,080
Okay, then.

218
00:11:02,470 --> 00:11:04,190
So, tell your dad

219
00:11:04,220 --> 00:11:05,950
which day and which train it is.

220
00:11:07,410 --> 00:11:07,820
Okay.

221
00:11:08,370 --> 00:11:08,840
Answer it,

222
00:11:08,840 --> 00:11:09,700
or I'll hang up.

223
00:11:13,410 --> 00:11:15,090
Look at you! You always do it this way.

224
00:11:15,090 --> 00:11:16,230
Fine, then.

225
00:11:17,770 --> 00:11:18,430
Hello, Dad.

226
00:11:19,530 --> 00:11:20,530
I'm telling you,

227
00:11:20,890 --> 00:11:22,890
watch your belongings on the train.

228
00:11:24,840 --> 00:11:26,650
Well, my train will leave on the 25th,

229
00:11:26,650 --> 00:11:27,960
at about 7 a.m.,

230
00:11:27,980 --> 00:11:29,100
and I'll arrive in Yantai.

231
00:11:29,100 --> 00:11:30,620
Then I'll be home in half an hour.

232
00:11:30,620 --> 00:11:31,350
Got it.

233
00:11:39,800 --> 00:11:40,640
I see.

234
00:11:41,530 --> 00:11:43,010
"Got it"? What did you get?

235
00:11:43,030 --> 00:11:45,010
You haven't even asked him
which day he's coming back.

236
00:11:45,010 --> 00:11:46,070
I got it!

237
00:11:46,910 --> 00:11:47,600
Jeez!

238
00:11:48,720 --> 00:11:50,150
This guy. Good grief.

239
00:11:50,960 --> 00:11:52,090
Where are you going?

240
00:11:52,510 --> 00:11:53,910
To buy some goods for the New Year.

241
00:11:53,910 --> 00:11:54,840
Where am I going?

242
00:11:55,910 --> 00:11:57,170
Goods for the New Year.

243
00:11:58,870 --> 00:11:59,530
If you're not going,

244
00:11:59,530 --> 00:12:01,330
what do you expect me to pay with?

245
00:12:01,410 --> 00:12:02,250
You don't have money, right?

246
00:12:02,250 --> 00:12:03,650
Isn't it obvious?

247
00:12:04,370 --> 00:12:06,530
Fine. Let's go buy goods for the New Year.

248
00:12:06,530 --> 00:12:07,510
Jeez...

249
00:12:07,670 --> 00:12:08,340
Let's go.

250
00:12:10,270 --> 00:12:11,070
Welcome back.

251
00:12:13,010 --> 00:12:14,810
You bought a whole lot of things.

252
00:12:17,720 --> 00:12:18,760
Yeah.

253
00:12:19,480 --> 00:12:20,100
Why do you look

254
00:12:20,100 --> 00:12:21,120
a little gloomy?

255
00:12:21,620 --> 00:12:22,130
These are all

256
00:12:22,130 --> 00:12:23,860
from the list my mom made for me.

257
00:12:24,030 --> 00:12:26,170
They're all
my brother's favorite foods and drinks.

258
00:12:26,170 --> 00:12:27,910
Not a single item can be missing.

259
00:12:27,910 --> 00:12:30,370
I've been to several streets
to get them all.

260
00:12:34,320 --> 00:12:35,220
Why do I feel like

261
00:12:35,220 --> 00:12:37,100
you can't bear to leave me?

262
00:12:37,740 --> 00:12:39,880
Of course I'm reluctant to part with you.

263
00:12:39,880 --> 00:12:41,480
Didn't I leave you my number?

264
00:12:41,910 --> 00:12:43,310
Call me when you get back.

265
00:12:44,600 --> 00:12:47,910
The day Mrs. Jiang and Xiaobao came,

266
00:12:48,400 --> 00:12:50,040
when we were having dinner,

267
00:12:50,290 --> 00:12:52,820
I really envied that kind of happiness.

268
00:12:53,550 --> 00:12:55,060
Don't laugh at me,

269
00:12:55,220 --> 00:12:57,280
but I actually made a wish in my heart.

270
00:12:57,620 --> 00:12:59,120
I wish we could spend

271
00:12:59,140 --> 00:13:01,540
the New Year together
like this every year.

272
00:13:01,550 --> 00:13:02,520
Honestly,

273
00:13:02,790 --> 00:13:03,290
I feel like

274
00:13:03,290 --> 00:13:05,790
the Seasons Change Hostel is
more like my home.

275
00:13:05,790 --> 00:13:07,120
This is indeed our home.

276
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:10,700
As long as it makes everyone happy,

277
00:13:10,700 --> 00:13:11,500
it is a home.

278
00:13:15,510 --> 00:13:16,040
Alright.

279
00:13:16,480 --> 00:13:18,150
Let's put up these couplets

280
00:13:18,150 --> 00:13:19,270
for our home.

281
00:13:20,530 --> 00:13:21,930
There are couplets, too?

282
00:13:22,530 --> 00:13:24,130
Shengli wrote them. Come on.

283
00:13:27,180 --> 00:13:28,400
How brilliant.

284
00:13:28,750 --> 00:13:29,280
Let's go.

285
00:13:33,340 --> 00:13:34,100
Luo.

286
00:13:34,340 --> 00:13:35,370
This lantern looks

287
00:13:35,370 --> 00:13:36,820
much bigger than last year's.

288
00:13:36,820 --> 00:13:37,910
If it were smaller, I'd be afraid

289
00:13:37,910 --> 00:13:39,320
you couldn't find your way back.

290
00:13:39,320 --> 00:13:40,020
Sublessor,

291
00:13:40,130 --> 00:13:41,960
you are even brighter
than this red lantern.

292
00:13:41,960 --> 00:13:43,080
That sounds

293
00:13:43,100 --> 00:13:45,460
even better
than those New Year's greetings.

294
00:13:45,460 --> 00:13:46,200
Luo, let me steady it for you.

295
00:13:46,200 --> 00:13:47,000
Don't bother.

296
00:13:47,000 --> 00:13:47,670
You guys should get going.

297
00:13:47,670 --> 00:13:48,660
Or you'll miss your train.

298
00:13:48,660 --> 00:13:49,250
Hurry up and go.

299
00:13:49,250 --> 00:13:50,310
All right. Come on.

300
00:13:50,360 --> 00:13:51,720
The doors
of the Seasons Change Hostel will

301
00:13:51,720 --> 00:13:52,840
always be open for you guys.

302
00:13:52,840 --> 00:13:53,400
Okay.

303
00:13:53,500 --> 00:13:54,350
Okay, Luo.

304
00:13:54,370 --> 00:13:56,360
-See you next year.
-Welcome back soon after the New Year.

305
00:13:56,360 --> 00:13:57,220
Happy New Year.

306
00:13:57,580 --> 00:13:59,790
Say hello to your family for me
when you get home.

307
00:13:59,790 --> 00:14:00,990
No problem! Goodbye!

308
00:14:02,250 --> 00:14:03,510
Ranran, Ranran.

309
00:14:04,310 --> 00:14:06,290
Why are you going back so suddenly?

310
00:14:06,290 --> 00:14:08,550
We haven't had a proper talk about us yet.

311
00:14:09,480 --> 00:14:10,720
What time is your train?

312
00:14:10,720 --> 00:14:11,790
How about we find a small restaurant

313
00:14:11,790 --> 00:14:12,870
and sit down for a chat?

314
00:14:12,870 --> 00:14:14,240
Let's just talk.

315
00:14:16,720 --> 00:14:19,050
There's nothing to talk about between us.

316
00:14:37,360 --> 00:14:39,290
Happy Spring Festival in advance.

317
00:14:53,650 --> 00:14:54,290
All set.

318
00:14:54,600 --> 00:14:55,060
Come on.

319
00:14:57,370 --> 00:14:58,290
Let's split them.

320
00:14:58,290 --> 00:14:58,860
Okay.

321
00:14:59,390 --> 00:15:01,500
You take 3 boxes of Daoxiangcun pastries.

322
00:15:01,500 --> 00:15:01,940
Your mom said

323
00:15:01,940 --> 00:15:03,870
she likes the jujube paste pastry.

324
00:15:04,240 --> 00:15:05,880
We agreed on 2 boxes each.

325
00:15:06,170 --> 00:15:07,120
It's fine.

326
00:15:07,910 --> 00:15:10,040
She's fond of the jujube paste pastry!

327
00:15:10,250 --> 00:15:11,980
One box is enough for my family.

328
00:15:13,120 --> 00:15:15,100
Alright, thank you on behalf of my mom.

329
00:15:15,100 --> 00:15:15,760
No problem.

330
00:15:17,360 --> 00:15:18,020
And this.

331
00:15:18,220 --> 00:15:19,880
My mom specially sent it over.

332
00:15:19,910 --> 00:15:21,440
It's her handmade sausage.

333
00:15:22,440 --> 00:15:23,510
Take it home and try it.

334
00:15:23,510 --> 00:15:24,840
If you like it,

335
00:15:25,200 --> 00:15:26,220
there are also cured ribs,

336
00:15:26,220 --> 00:15:27,120
cured ham, cured duck wings,

337
00:15:27,120 --> 00:15:27,870
and so much more.

338
00:15:27,870 --> 00:15:28,400
I like it!

339
00:15:28,860 --> 00:15:30,050
You haven't even tasted it yet.

340
00:15:30,050 --> 00:15:30,840
I just love it.

341
00:15:30,840 --> 00:15:31,910
My family likes it, too.

342
00:15:31,910 --> 00:15:33,080
I'm speaking for them.

343
00:15:33,080 --> 00:15:34,650
If so, you can have as much as you like.

344
00:15:34,650 --> 00:15:35,080
Okay.

345
00:15:39,740 --> 00:15:41,470
Alright, everything's ready.

346
00:15:42,510 --> 00:15:43,840
There's one more thing.

347
00:15:43,940 --> 00:15:44,770
What else?

348
00:15:48,910 --> 00:15:49,730
Who is it for?

349
00:15:49,960 --> 00:15:50,690
It's for you.

350
00:15:50,840 --> 00:15:52,100
Open it and take a look.

351
00:15:55,960 --> 00:15:56,960
A New Year's gift?

352
00:16:02,410 --> 00:16:03,200
The number is

353
00:16:03,200 --> 00:16:05,780
126, extension 2935092.

354
00:16:06,290 --> 00:16:07,130
Tell your family

355
00:16:07,130 --> 00:16:08,320
this number when you go back.

356
00:16:08,320 --> 00:16:09,120
You'll know immediately

357
00:16:09,120 --> 00:16:10,720
if anyone wants to reach you.

358
00:16:12,310 --> 00:16:14,200
I'll get a pen to write it down for you.

359
00:16:14,200 --> 00:16:14,830
Hold on.

360
00:16:24,980 --> 00:16:25,910
Write with this.

361
00:16:27,890 --> 00:16:28,720
Hero?

362
00:16:29,770 --> 00:16:32,870
Is... Is this... for me?

363
00:16:39,650 --> 00:16:40,580
Write it on this.

364
00:16:41,120 --> 00:16:41,860
Let me try.

365
00:16:50,040 --> 00:16:52,270
[126, extension 2935092]

366
00:16:52,700 --> 00:16:54,160
This pen is really smooth.

367
00:16:55,680 --> 00:16:57,410
Then use it every day from now on

368
00:16:57,410 --> 00:16:59,210
to write scripts, good scripts.

369
00:17:00,620 --> 00:17:02,350
I'll also use it to write you...

370
00:17:02,670 --> 00:17:03,870
w-write you letters.

371
00:17:05,280 --> 00:17:07,339
Are you good at writing love letters?

372
00:17:09,200 --> 00:17:11,700
I've never written a love letter.

373
00:17:11,730 --> 00:17:12,190
Well,

374
00:17:12,510 --> 00:17:13,660
but I'm a screenwriter!

375
00:17:13,660 --> 00:17:15,109
I... I can compose it.

376
00:17:16,990 --> 00:17:17,849
Where is yours?

377
00:17:19,619 --> 00:17:20,619
I only bought one.

378
00:17:22,119 --> 00:17:22,900
Finally,

379
00:17:22,900 --> 00:17:24,180
we have a communication tool,

380
00:17:24,180 --> 00:17:25,180
but it's one-way?

381
00:17:25,880 --> 00:17:27,210
Only you can contact me?

382
00:17:27,230 --> 00:17:28,079
Well,

383
00:17:28,210 --> 00:17:29,780
one of these isn't cheap.

384
00:17:30,050 --> 00:17:31,420
Besides, you're a girl.

385
00:17:31,420 --> 00:17:32,740
If you can be reached at any time,

386
00:17:32,740 --> 00:17:35,070
we'll feel more at ease, right?

387
00:17:51,220 --> 00:17:53,710
[Yantai]

388
00:17:53,880 --> 00:17:54,830
Shengli, you're back!

389
00:17:54,830 --> 00:17:55,330
Hi, madam.

390
00:17:55,330 --> 00:17:56,250
Back for the New Year?

391
00:17:56,250 --> 00:17:57,040
Yes.

392
00:18:16,030 --> 00:18:17,360
What are you looking at?

393
00:18:17,620 --> 00:18:18,750
Don't recognize me?

394
00:18:22,560 --> 00:18:23,490
Let's go inside.

395
00:18:33,310 --> 00:18:34,050
Hua.

396
00:18:34,980 --> 00:18:36,050
Our son is back.

397
00:18:39,010 --> 00:18:39,660
Mom!

398
00:18:41,540 --> 00:18:42,800
My son is back!

399
00:18:45,660 --> 00:18:47,300
Let Mom hug you.

400
00:18:47,930 --> 00:18:49,060
I missed you so much.

401
00:18:49,300 --> 00:18:50,300
Let me look at you.

402
00:18:51,700 --> 00:18:52,610
Why did you lose weight?

403
00:18:52,610 --> 00:18:53,570
I didn't!

404
00:18:53,590 --> 00:18:54,180
Did you

405
00:18:54,180 --> 00:18:55,180
not eat well in Beijing?

406
00:18:55,180 --> 00:18:56,110
I ate very well!

407
00:18:56,110 --> 00:18:57,770
I ate a lot in Beijing!

408
00:18:57,770 --> 00:18:59,030
My heart aches for you.

409
00:18:59,050 --> 00:19:00,910
Mom, I really didn't lose weight.

410
00:19:01,010 --> 00:19:01,500
My heart aches.

411
00:19:01,500 --> 00:19:02,500
Alright, enough.

412
00:19:03,740 --> 00:19:05,140
Is the food ready?

413
00:19:05,200 --> 00:19:06,030
It's ready.

414
00:19:06,090 --> 00:19:07,070
I only need to take it out of the pot.

415
00:19:07,070 --> 00:19:07,980
Hurry up.

416
00:19:08,270 --> 00:19:09,290
Take off your coat

417
00:19:09,290 --> 00:19:10,060
and have some water.

418
00:19:10,060 --> 00:19:10,420
Okay.

419
00:19:10,460 --> 00:19:11,660
It will be ready soon.

420
00:19:19,090 --> 00:19:20,640
Look how happy your mom is.

421
00:19:21,230 --> 00:19:23,700
[Wenzhou]

422
00:19:25,640 --> 00:19:26,610
It's so good to be home.

423
00:19:26,610 --> 00:19:27,610
Missed home, huh?

424
00:19:28,590 --> 00:19:29,640
I missed my mom.

425
00:19:33,790 --> 00:19:34,240
Come on.

426
00:19:34,060 --> 00:19:36,270
[Huzhou]

427
00:19:34,240 --> 00:19:35,870
Mom, I'm back!

428
00:19:36,070 --> 00:19:37,720
You're back so early!

429
00:19:37,770 --> 00:19:39,830
Hello, Mrs. Zhang, Mrs. Wang, Mr. Li.

430
00:19:40,460 --> 00:19:41,380
This tile...

431
00:19:42,140 --> 00:19:43,000
I win.

432
00:19:44,330 --> 00:19:45,110
You win?

433
00:19:45,850 --> 00:19:48,050
You've been the only one
winning the whole time.

434
00:19:48,050 --> 00:19:49,050
You're back, sis!

435
00:19:49,310 --> 00:19:50,130
I'm back.

436
00:19:50,310 --> 00:19:51,140
Help me carry some.

437
00:19:51,140 --> 00:19:52,410
Are these all for me?

438
00:20:03,780 --> 00:20:06,420
[Shanxi]

439
00:20:27,550 --> 00:20:27,980
Dad.

440
00:20:29,730 --> 00:20:30,410
Son,

441
00:20:31,190 --> 00:20:31,920
you're back.

442
00:20:43,670 --> 00:20:46,050
[Henan]

443
00:20:48,590 --> 00:20:49,500
We're home!

444
00:20:49,500 --> 00:20:51,030
We're home for the New Year!

445
00:21:11,970 --> 00:21:13,170
What brings you here?

446
00:21:15,010 --> 00:21:16,210
You're having a meal?

447
00:21:16,940 --> 00:21:18,870
I'm here to add some dishes for you.

448
00:21:18,940 --> 00:21:19,850
I brought you

449
00:21:19,850 --> 00:21:20,960
hot dumplings

450
00:21:21,440 --> 00:21:22,700
and a big pork knuckle.

451
00:21:23,320 --> 00:21:25,250
We should eat well for the New Year.

452
00:21:27,270 --> 00:21:28,550
I thought you had gone back

453
00:21:28,550 --> 00:21:30,350
to your hometown
after we had a meal last week.

454
00:21:30,350 --> 00:21:31,840
Close the door.

455
00:21:31,860 --> 00:21:32,990
Don't you feel cold?

456
00:21:34,880 --> 00:21:36,050
T-Then you...

457
00:21:39,530 --> 00:21:40,760
What do you mean?

458
00:21:44,410 --> 00:21:46,370
If you don't want me here,

459
00:21:46,400 --> 00:21:46,960
I'll leave.

460
00:21:46,960 --> 00:21:48,400
No, no, I...

461
00:21:54,940 --> 00:21:56,140
Take off your coat.

462
00:21:56,170 --> 00:21:58,370
It's letting the remaining cold air in.

463
00:21:58,940 --> 00:21:59,850
Take a seat.

464
00:22:02,900 --> 00:22:03,760
It's still hot.

465
00:22:05,070 --> 00:22:06,130
Is it cold outside?

466
00:22:06,400 --> 00:22:07,630
Freezing cold.

467
00:22:09,790 --> 00:22:11,590
You even brought the little pot.

468
00:22:11,790 --> 00:22:13,650
Be careful, don't burn yourself.

469
00:22:18,200 --> 00:22:19,530
This huge pork knuckle!

470
00:22:20,330 --> 00:22:21,370
Not bad, right?

471
00:22:22,170 --> 00:22:23,030
It's great.

472
00:22:25,460 --> 00:22:27,060
You haven't answered me yet.

473
00:22:27,220 --> 00:22:28,200
It's the New Year,

474
00:22:28,200 --> 00:22:29,090
and you didn't go back home.

475
00:22:29,090 --> 00:22:30,290
What brings you here?

476
00:22:32,380 --> 00:22:33,590
My home is far away.

477
00:22:33,920 --> 00:22:35,640
My parents are doing alright

478
00:22:35,640 --> 00:22:36,640
at home together.

479
00:22:37,610 --> 00:22:40,060
I'm also used to being alone.

480
00:22:41,030 --> 00:22:42,290
Aren't you alone, too?

481
00:22:43,310 --> 00:22:44,050
I don't have any relatives left

482
00:22:44,050 --> 00:22:45,850
in my hometown in the Northeast.

483
00:22:48,640 --> 00:22:49,530
My parents passed away

484
00:22:49,530 --> 00:22:50,790
when I was very little.

485
00:22:51,660 --> 00:22:52,990
I'm actually an orphan.

486
00:22:53,680 --> 00:22:55,810
When I first came to Beijing by myself,

487
00:22:56,070 --> 00:22:57,660
it was the boss
of this Seasons Change Hostel

488
00:22:57,660 --> 00:22:58,460
who took me in.

489
00:22:59,570 --> 00:23:01,370
I treat this place as my own home.

490
00:23:02,510 --> 00:23:03,970
I treat them all as family.

491
00:23:05,420 --> 00:23:06,940
But when the New Year comes,

492
00:23:06,940 --> 00:23:08,090
they all go home.

493
00:23:09,330 --> 00:23:10,160
I'm used to it.

494
00:23:17,300 --> 00:23:18,050
Lili.

495
00:23:20,440 --> 00:23:21,290
The past few times we met,

496
00:23:21,290 --> 00:23:23,420
there was something I didn't tell you.

497
00:23:24,420 --> 00:23:26,180
This hostel looks quite big, right?

498
00:23:26,180 --> 00:23:27,710
Actually, I'm not the boss.

499
00:23:29,200 --> 00:23:30,840
I'm just a worker

500
00:23:30,920 --> 00:23:32,850
to look after the shop for the boss.

501
00:23:38,630 --> 00:23:40,450
No one's taken you for the boss.

502
00:23:40,980 --> 00:23:42,910
You've never taken me for the boss?

503
00:23:43,720 --> 00:23:45,010
I like to show off a bit

504
00:23:45,030 --> 00:23:46,290
in front of the others.

505
00:23:48,070 --> 00:23:49,670
But I don't want to lie to you.

506
00:23:56,500 --> 00:23:58,030
Now that I've made it clear,

507
00:23:58,610 --> 00:23:59,850
I feel relieved.

508
00:24:01,290 --> 00:24:03,940
You feel relieved, and then?

509
00:24:05,090 --> 00:24:06,700
Then you can just ask me whatever else

510
00:24:06,700 --> 00:24:07,400
you want to know.

511
00:24:07,400 --> 00:24:08,860
I'll tell you everything.

512
00:24:11,500 --> 00:24:12,730
Hurry up and eat.

513
00:24:12,900 --> 00:24:14,760
We have plenty of time ahead of us.

514
00:24:16,250 --> 00:24:17,040
Really?

515
00:24:33,110 --> 00:24:35,010
I'll go close the front door.

516
00:24:36,030 --> 00:24:38,030
The Seasons Change Hostel is
celebrating the New Year!

517
00:24:38,030 --> 00:24:40,340
Well... This is...

518
00:24:45,310 --> 00:24:46,700
The last dish is coming.

519
00:24:47,250 --> 00:24:47,910
Here you go.

520
00:24:52,480 --> 00:24:53,570
I put it on.

521
00:24:53,640 --> 00:24:54,310
Isn't it nice?

522
00:24:54,310 --> 00:24:55,770
It looks great on you, Mom.

523
00:24:56,200 --> 00:24:56,770
It looks good.

524
00:24:56,770 --> 00:24:58,030
Look at my son's taste.

525
00:24:58,090 --> 00:24:58,920
It's so good.

526
00:24:58,940 --> 00:25:00,700
It's both beautiful and festive.

527
00:25:00,700 --> 00:25:01,780
It suits you so well.

528
00:25:01,780 --> 00:25:02,720
Thank you, son.

529
00:25:04,150 --> 00:25:05,000
Why don't you wear yours?

530
00:25:05,000 --> 00:25:06,200
Our son bought one for you, too.

531
00:25:06,200 --> 00:25:07,940
Me? If I wore it, you'd cook?

532
00:25:08,050 --> 00:25:09,650
Who'd go cook in the kitchen?

533
00:25:09,880 --> 00:25:12,030
Your dad is treasuring it so much.

534
00:25:12,070 --> 00:25:13,090
Then wear it tomorrow.

535
00:25:13,090 --> 00:25:14,890
Wear it when you're not cooking.

536
00:25:15,270 --> 00:25:16,820
Son, you know what?

537
00:25:17,030 --> 00:25:18,110
These dishes were

538
00:25:19,810 --> 00:25:21,310
all prepared by your dad.

539
00:25:21,600 --> 00:25:22,220
Your dad's been

540
00:25:22,220 --> 00:25:23,680
preparing
for tonight's New Year's Eve dinner

541
00:25:23,680 --> 00:25:25,440
for quite a long time.

542
00:25:26,760 --> 00:25:27,990
He cooked them all.

543
00:25:39,200 --> 00:25:40,790
Dad, Mom.

544
00:25:42,070 --> 00:25:43,130
Over the past half year,

545
00:25:43,130 --> 00:25:44,590
I was drifting in Beijing,

546
00:25:45,240 --> 00:25:46,440
making you two worry.

547
00:25:46,530 --> 00:25:47,930
This first glass of wine,

548
00:25:48,770 --> 00:25:50,100
I'd like to toast to you.

549
00:25:50,560 --> 00:25:53,400
We won't be worried after New Year's Eve?

550
00:25:54,810 --> 00:25:57,070
You've only been in Beijing
for a short time.

551
00:25:57,070 --> 00:25:58,870
How did you start drinking wine?

552
00:25:59,750 --> 00:26:00,140
I...

553
00:26:00,160 --> 00:26:01,600
It's New Year's Eve!

554
00:26:02,050 --> 00:26:02,970
We're having fun!

555
00:26:02,970 --> 00:26:03,920
Even I want to have a drink, too.

556
00:26:03,920 --> 00:26:04,820
Son, go ahead.

557
00:26:04,850 --> 00:26:05,980
Pour me a glass, too.

558
00:26:06,220 --> 00:26:07,010
No more soft drinks.

559
00:26:07,010 --> 00:26:08,000
Mom, have this one.

560
00:26:08,000 --> 00:26:08,730
Wait, you...

561
00:26:08,770 --> 00:26:09,300
Alright.

562
00:26:09,610 --> 00:26:10,070
Come on.

563
00:26:11,780 --> 00:26:12,700
Come on, son.

564
00:26:13,000 --> 00:26:14,500
I wish you greater progress

565
00:26:14,500 --> 00:26:16,360
in the new year!

566
00:26:17,400 --> 00:26:18,050
Hurry.

567
00:26:18,660 --> 00:26:19,200
Fine, fine.

568
00:26:19,200 --> 00:26:20,030
Your son is toasting you.

569
00:26:20,030 --> 00:26:20,500
Come on.

570
00:26:20,500 --> 00:26:21,560
Stand up, stand up.

571
00:26:22,000 --> 00:26:24,790
-Come on. Let's have a drink together.
-Happy New Year.

572
00:26:24,790 --> 00:26:26,270
Let's get better and better
in the new year.

573
00:26:26,270 --> 00:26:27,530
Get better and better.

574
00:26:41,070 --> 00:26:42,130
This second glass,

575
00:26:42,130 --> 00:26:43,930
Dad, I'd like to toast to you.

576
00:26:44,850 --> 00:26:45,330
Well,

577
00:26:45,350 --> 00:26:47,580
thanks to your goading back then,

578
00:26:47,840 --> 00:26:49,200
it made me burn my bridges

579
00:26:49,200 --> 00:26:50,330
and fight with my back to the wall.

580
00:26:50,330 --> 00:26:51,860
I didn't force you to leave.

581
00:26:52,980 --> 00:26:54,940
You insisted on leaving yourself.

582
00:26:55,420 --> 00:26:57,220
Alright, stop acting so tough.

583
00:26:57,440 --> 00:26:58,940
My son's name is listed

584
00:26:58,940 --> 00:27:00,770
right after the great screenwriter's.

585
00:27:00,770 --> 00:27:02,270
It's really something worth celebrating.

586
00:27:02,270 --> 00:27:03,130
Come on, son...

587
00:27:03,770 --> 00:27:04,810
You haven't poured wine for your dad yet.

588
00:27:04,810 --> 00:27:05,940
Hurry up and pour it.

589
00:27:06,270 --> 00:27:07,400
You're too nervous.

590
00:27:09,540 --> 00:27:09,940
Okay.

591
00:27:09,940 --> 00:27:12,470
Mom, we haven't even
started shooting it yet.

592
00:27:12,620 --> 00:27:14,450
The fact that they paid you is

593
00:27:14,650 --> 00:27:16,180
a recognition of your work.

594
00:27:16,290 --> 00:27:17,220
They'll shoot it

595
00:27:17,220 --> 00:27:18,500
sooner or later.

596
00:27:18,510 --> 00:27:19,700
Come on, congratulations.

597
00:27:19,700 --> 00:27:20,510
Congratulations!

598
00:27:20,510 --> 00:27:21,880
Congratulations!

599
00:27:22,590 --> 00:27:23,450
It's good news.

600
00:27:31,550 --> 00:27:32,660
You've grown up.

601
00:27:34,320 --> 00:27:35,450
Son, you know what?

602
00:27:35,490 --> 00:27:36,940
Your dad once told me,

603
00:27:37,770 --> 00:27:38,820
"In the future,

604
00:27:38,850 --> 00:27:39,900
when our son's movie is

605
00:27:39,900 --> 00:27:40,790
released

606
00:27:40,790 --> 00:27:41,800
in theaters,

607
00:27:41,980 --> 00:27:43,200
I will take

608
00:27:43,200 --> 00:27:44,240
all the relatives we know

609
00:27:44,240 --> 00:27:45,100
to go watch it

610
00:27:45,180 --> 00:27:45,880
and point

611
00:27:45,880 --> 00:27:47,030
to the name on the screen and say,

612
00:27:47,030 --> 00:27:48,770
'Look, that's my son!'"

613
00:27:48,810 --> 00:27:50,160
Alright... Enough.

614
00:27:50,200 --> 00:27:51,510
Come on, stop it.

615
00:27:52,170 --> 00:27:53,350
We haven't started eating the dishes,

616
00:27:53,350 --> 00:27:55,370
yet we've already had
several glasses of wine.

617
00:27:55,370 --> 00:27:55,940
When will you

618
00:27:55,940 --> 00:27:56,900
finish talking?

619
00:27:57,070 --> 00:27:58,250
Isn't it time for us to eat now?

620
00:27:58,250 --> 00:27:59,450
I'm just happy.

621
00:27:59,570 --> 00:28:00,590
Happy, happy.

622
00:28:00,860 --> 00:28:01,420
Mom,

623
00:28:01,420 --> 00:28:02,590
how come I find my dad

624
00:28:02,590 --> 00:28:04,310
much gentler this time I'm back?

625
00:28:04,310 --> 00:28:04,850
Right?

626
00:28:06,980 --> 00:28:08,110
Then how about this?

627
00:28:08,420 --> 00:28:10,090
I'd like to have one last toast.

628
00:28:10,090 --> 00:28:11,680
Right, three toasts, three.

629
00:28:11,680 --> 00:28:12,660
In the new year,

630
00:28:13,110 --> 00:28:14,270
I wish you both

631
00:28:14,520 --> 00:28:15,710
good health

632
00:28:16,270 --> 00:28:17,980
and happiness every day.

633
00:28:18,610 --> 00:28:19,030
Okay.

634
00:28:19,140 --> 00:28:20,690
I wish you both well.

635
00:28:20,770 --> 00:28:21,690
Okay.

636
00:28:22,550 --> 00:28:23,210
Come on.

637
00:28:23,230 --> 00:28:23,900
Cheers.

638
00:28:31,790 --> 00:28:32,290
Come on.

639
00:28:32,700 --> 00:28:33,720
Let's eat up.

640
00:28:34,480 --> 00:28:36,570
We have a great screenwriter
in the family.

641
00:28:36,570 --> 00:28:37,570
Having a New Year's Eve dinner is

642
00:28:37,570 --> 00:28:39,570
almost like acting in a sketch

643
00:28:39,610 --> 00:28:41,210
on the Spring Festival Gala.

644
00:28:41,330 --> 00:28:42,500
Isn't that great?

645
00:28:42,500 --> 00:28:43,830
We are putting on our own show first.

646
00:28:43,830 --> 00:28:45,230
Come on, son. Try this.

647
00:28:45,290 --> 00:28:46,690
Alright, stop drinking.

648
00:28:47,000 --> 00:28:47,830
Have some juice.

649
00:28:47,830 --> 00:28:49,090
You've drunk too much.

650
00:28:50,330 --> 00:28:51,270
Eat more.

651
00:28:51,270 --> 00:28:52,800
Come on, you have some, too.

652
00:28:52,810 --> 00:28:53,430
Okay.

653
00:28:53,500 --> 00:28:53,770
Eat up.

654
00:28:53,770 --> 00:28:54,660
I can reach it.

655
00:28:55,000 --> 00:28:55,960
Look at all these ingredients

656
00:28:55,960 --> 00:28:57,330
your dad bought

657
00:28:57,440 --> 00:28:58,840
from the morning market.

658
00:28:59,000 --> 00:28:59,700
Eat more.

659
00:29:01,530 --> 00:29:02,460
How is it? Take a bite.

660
00:29:02,460 --> 00:29:03,090
Delicious!

661
00:29:03,090 --> 00:29:03,570
Is it good?

662
00:29:03,570 --> 00:29:04,010
Yeah!

663
00:29:04,270 --> 00:29:06,530
How is it compared to your mom's cooking?

664
00:29:06,900 --> 00:29:08,720
It's just that your cooking is
not as good as Mom's.

665
00:29:08,720 --> 00:29:09,320
Right?

666
00:29:11,980 --> 00:29:13,460
Well... alright.

667
00:29:13,550 --> 00:29:13,940
See?

668
00:29:13,940 --> 00:29:15,610
My son is still on my side.

669
00:29:21,750 --> 00:29:22,410
Hey, you...

670
00:29:27,440 --> 00:29:28,570
I want another bowl.

671
00:29:30,570 --> 00:29:32,230
Serve a bowl for your brother.

672
00:29:40,080 --> 00:29:42,010
Sis, didn't you say

673
00:29:42,330 --> 00:29:43,920
you would buy me a pager?

674
00:29:44,090 --> 00:29:45,960
Yeah, I heard it.

675
00:29:50,070 --> 00:29:52,080
Pagers are so expensive.

676
00:29:52,240 --> 00:29:52,790
Didn't I

677
00:29:52,790 --> 00:29:54,270
buy you game cartridges?

678
00:29:54,550 --> 00:29:55,940
A game console is a game console,

679
00:29:55,940 --> 00:29:57,200
and a pager is a pager.

680
00:29:57,250 --> 00:29:58,650
Then give them back to me.

681
00:30:05,420 --> 00:30:07,020
Are you wearing new clothes?

682
00:30:08,330 --> 00:30:09,610
The girl I live with, who's older than me,

683
00:30:09,610 --> 00:30:10,470
lent them to me.

684
00:30:11,640 --> 00:30:12,290
Are there still

685
00:30:12,290 --> 00:30:14,050
such kind girls in the world?

686
00:30:15,830 --> 00:30:16,890
When girls grow up,

687
00:30:16,900 --> 00:30:18,430
they start spending money.

688
00:30:18,980 --> 00:30:20,780
Look how rough my hands are now.

689
00:30:22,810 --> 00:30:25,140
Ever since you were little, I enrolled you

690
00:30:25,380 --> 00:30:26,250
in all sorts of classes

691
00:30:26,250 --> 00:30:28,530
like the eloquence and dance ones.

692
00:30:29,660 --> 00:30:31,190
They were all investments.

693
00:30:32,380 --> 00:30:33,420
You're not thinking

694
00:30:33,420 --> 00:30:34,750
about the family at all.

695
00:30:35,380 --> 00:30:36,000
Mom,

696
00:30:36,850 --> 00:30:38,720
I know things haven't been easy for you,

697
00:30:38,720 --> 00:30:40,250
and I'm making great efforts, too.

698
00:30:40,250 --> 00:30:41,110
Efforts

699
00:30:41,550 --> 00:30:42,980
need to yield results.

700
00:30:45,550 --> 00:30:47,210
What do you mean by "results"?

701
00:30:47,590 --> 00:30:48,240
Money?

702
00:30:50,980 --> 00:30:51,570
Ranran,

703
00:30:51,940 --> 00:30:52,810
let's not talk about

704
00:30:52,810 --> 00:30:53,880
how much I've done for you.

705
00:30:53,880 --> 00:30:55,810
Just look at your younger brother, Fufu.

706
00:30:55,810 --> 00:30:57,070
Didn't he also

707
00:30:57,310 --> 00:30:58,770
give away his college fund

708
00:30:58,830 --> 00:31:02,110
to support your acting in Beijing?

709
00:31:03,270 --> 00:31:06,070
Didn't he fail
the college entrance exam himself?

710
00:31:09,400 --> 00:31:10,550
We are family.

711
00:31:10,550 --> 00:31:12,000
You shouldn't say that.

712
00:31:12,110 --> 00:31:12,790
Right?

713
00:31:13,000 --> 00:31:14,940
Giving goes both ways.

714
00:31:15,110 --> 00:31:17,920
Your brother has a girlfriend now.

715
00:31:18,140 --> 00:31:20,070
You should also take that to heart.

716
00:31:22,240 --> 00:31:22,850
Sis,

717
00:31:23,090 --> 00:31:24,090
when is your TV drama

718
00:31:24,090 --> 00:31:25,140
going to air?

719
00:31:26,350 --> 00:31:27,280
I don't know yet.

720
00:31:28,700 --> 00:31:30,010
Which supporting role are you?

721
00:31:30,010 --> 00:31:30,940
A very minor one.

722
00:31:32,090 --> 00:31:32,940
A minor one?

723
00:31:33,140 --> 00:31:34,330
Can you even be seen?

724
00:31:34,500 --> 00:31:36,430
The scene will flash by in a second.

725
00:31:41,000 --> 00:31:41,550
Mom.

726
00:31:43,200 --> 00:31:44,330
As big as Beijing is,

727
00:31:45,440 --> 00:31:47,300
not everyone there gets a chance.

728
00:31:49,380 --> 00:31:50,380
You must have one.

729
00:31:51,220 --> 00:31:52,550
I'm not pressuring you,

730
00:31:52,750 --> 00:31:55,030
but a woman's beauty
only lasts for a few years.

731
00:31:55,030 --> 00:31:56,490
If you don't work hard now,

732
00:31:56,750 --> 00:31:57,980
what are you waiting for?

733
00:31:57,980 --> 00:31:58,890
Besides,

734
00:31:58,960 --> 00:31:59,750
in a few years,

735
00:31:59,750 --> 00:32:01,440
you'll get married and have kids.

736
00:32:01,440 --> 00:32:01,940
Do you think

737
00:32:01,940 --> 00:32:03,980
you can still chase your dream
of becoming a star?

738
00:32:03,980 --> 00:32:04,980
No way!

739
00:32:07,440 --> 00:32:08,000
Mom,

740
00:32:09,420 --> 00:32:10,550
believe me.

741
00:32:11,310 --> 00:32:12,790
I can be a good actress.

742
00:32:13,640 --> 00:32:15,900
I will... I will work very hard.

743
00:32:19,240 --> 00:32:19,900
Here, Fufu.

744
00:32:20,830 --> 00:32:21,890
Fufu, here you are.

745
00:32:23,050 --> 00:32:23,980
The fish I fried.

746
00:32:26,900 --> 00:32:29,230
Mom, Dad, I wish you good health

747
00:32:29,500 --> 00:32:32,250
and all the best in the new year.

748
00:32:32,310 --> 00:32:32,800
Nice.

749
00:32:32,900 --> 00:32:33,940
Happy New Year.

750
00:32:33,940 --> 00:32:34,550
Yeah.

751
00:32:35,640 --> 00:32:36,500
Happy New Year.

752
00:32:36,790 --> 00:32:37,650
Happy New Year.

753
00:32:49,970 --> 00:32:53,810
♪ That winter snow ♪

754
00:32:56,520 --> 00:33:00,360
♪ Buried all the longing ♪

755
00:32:59,310 --> 00:33:00,710
I will sing a song for you,

756
00:33:00,720 --> 00:33:02,200
"The Ocean, My Hometown."

757
00:33:03,810 --> 00:33:07,440
♪ There's no going back ♪

758
00:33:08,240 --> 00:33:13,250
♪ Luckily, you're here with me ♪

759
00:33:18,740 --> 00:33:25,080
♪ All along the way ♪

760
00:33:25,670 --> 00:33:30,700
♪ Dreams bloom ♪

761
00:33:32,340 --> 00:33:37,310
♪ When starlight meets the sea ♪

762
00:33:38,200 --> 00:33:44,710
♪ I get to know your love ♪

763
00:33:45,440 --> 00:33:50,970
♪ All along the way ♪

764
00:33:52,190 --> 00:33:57,150
♪ Dreams bloom ♪

765
00:33:58,600 --> 00:34:03,750
♪ When the long night ends ♪

766
00:34:01,000 --> 00:34:03,680
This bonfire this year is bigger
than ever.

767
00:34:03,790 --> 00:34:05,290
Prosperous! It's a good omen.

768
00:34:04,480 --> 00:34:13,679
♪ Day is breaking ♪

769
00:34:05,660 --> 00:34:06,410
Have some dumplings.

770
00:34:06,410 --> 00:34:06,900
Kid,

771
00:34:07,610 --> 00:34:08,420
wish you

772
00:34:08,989 --> 00:34:11,110
a booming career in Beijing.

773
00:34:19,170 --> 00:34:21,090
Mom, where is Mr. Ye?

774
00:34:21,270 --> 00:34:23,420
He went to Chen's house
to deliver something.

775
00:34:23,420 --> 00:34:24,400
Their child is 100 days old,

776
00:34:24,400 --> 00:34:26,330
so they ordered 100-family cloth.

777
00:34:27,500 --> 00:34:29,030
Come on, try it.

778
00:34:38,010 --> 00:34:39,610
Shengli went back
to his hometown for the New Year?

779
00:34:39,610 --> 00:34:40,510
"Shengli"?

780
00:34:41,380 --> 00:34:43,909
You're addressing him
in such a friendly way.

781
00:34:45,460 --> 00:34:46,500
He called us

782
00:34:46,500 --> 00:34:48,030
at home many times

783
00:34:48,350 --> 00:34:49,090
and brought you

784
00:34:49,090 --> 00:34:50,420
so much delicious food.

785
00:34:50,610 --> 00:34:51,460
I also paid

786
00:34:51,460 --> 00:34:52,719
for these items, okay?

787
00:34:53,690 --> 00:34:55,590
A few calls, and you've been bought off?

788
00:34:55,590 --> 00:34:56,300
Look at you.

789
00:34:56,710 --> 00:34:58,180
If I didn't like him,

790
00:34:59,000 --> 00:35:00,400
wouldn't you be anxious?

791
00:35:01,650 --> 00:35:02,380
I think you're the one

792
00:35:02,380 --> 00:35:04,040
who's quickly taken his side.

793
00:35:04,340 --> 00:35:05,380
That's because I think

794
00:35:05,380 --> 00:35:06,880
Shengli is a nice guy.

795
00:35:07,380 --> 00:35:08,150
That's why.

796
00:35:09,610 --> 00:35:11,070
You haven't even met him yet.

797
00:35:11,070 --> 00:35:12,330
Yes, I haven't met him.

798
00:35:13,440 --> 00:35:15,010
But I know my daughter well.

799
00:35:15,280 --> 00:35:16,680
I can tell whether you're

800
00:35:17,150 --> 00:35:18,260
doing well or not.

801
00:35:23,900 --> 00:35:25,730
Your daughter is really capable.

802
00:35:25,730 --> 00:35:27,190
I can do fine wherever I go.

803
00:35:27,340 --> 00:35:28,030
Of course.

804
00:35:28,320 --> 00:35:30,570
My daughter has been really something
since childhood.

805
00:35:30,570 --> 00:35:32,170
I know it better than anyone.

806
00:35:37,300 --> 00:35:39,160
But no matter how capable you are,

807
00:35:40,260 --> 00:35:41,190
you'll always be

808
00:35:42,170 --> 00:35:43,530
just a kid to me.

809
00:35:45,360 --> 00:35:47,380
You were out there fighting on your own,

810
00:35:47,380 --> 00:35:48,150
and I was

811
00:35:49,130 --> 00:35:50,330
worried sick as well.

812
00:35:51,800 --> 00:35:52,320
But when I heard

813
00:35:52,320 --> 00:35:53,860
your voice on the phone,

814
00:35:54,150 --> 00:35:54,820
I knew

815
00:35:54,940 --> 00:35:56,400
you were doing well there.

816
00:35:57,280 --> 00:35:58,300
That put my mind

817
00:35:58,880 --> 00:36:00,130
at ease right away.

818
00:36:01,300 --> 00:36:03,270
Later, Shengli called me,

819
00:36:03,460 --> 00:36:04,380
and I knew

820
00:36:04,880 --> 00:36:06,630
someone was taking care of you.

821
00:36:07,860 --> 00:36:09,460
Then he must be a good person.

822
00:36:10,480 --> 00:36:12,010
At least he treats you well.

823
00:36:12,230 --> 00:36:14,090
That is the most important thing.

824
00:36:16,880 --> 00:36:19,110
The people
at the hostel are all so nice to me.

825
00:36:19,110 --> 00:36:19,710
That's because

826
00:36:19,710 --> 00:36:21,190
you are also nice to others.

827
00:36:21,190 --> 00:36:23,090
What goes around comes around.

828
00:36:24,320 --> 00:36:25,850
When you are away from home,

829
00:36:26,010 --> 00:36:27,210
lend a hand to others

830
00:36:27,340 --> 00:36:28,230
when you can.

831
00:36:28,940 --> 00:36:30,200
I've kept that in mind.

832
00:36:40,380 --> 00:36:41,260
It's so good.

833
00:36:46,320 --> 00:36:47,730
I don't know how Xu Shengli

834
00:36:47,730 --> 00:36:48,420
got to know

835
00:36:48,420 --> 00:36:49,570
that you like this.

836
00:36:53,530 --> 00:36:54,210
That day,

837
00:36:54,630 --> 00:36:56,170
he called for an interview

838
00:36:57,130 --> 00:36:59,400
and got sidetracked.

839
00:36:59,570 --> 00:37:01,460
He asked many things about our family

840
00:37:01,460 --> 00:37:01,900
and also asked

841
00:37:01,900 --> 00:37:03,300
about Mr. Ye's health.

842
00:37:04,050 --> 00:37:04,820
Then I got it.

843
00:37:06,190 --> 00:37:06,860
Actually,

844
00:37:07,530 --> 00:37:08,860
he was caring about you.

845
00:37:12,710 --> 00:37:13,910
That's just how he is.

846
00:37:14,630 --> 00:37:15,510
He really looks out

847
00:37:15,510 --> 00:37:16,790
for everyone.

848
00:37:17,980 --> 00:37:20,040
Then you should take good care of him.

849
00:37:20,060 --> 00:37:20,900
Control

850
00:37:22,260 --> 00:37:23,590
your temper sometimes.

851
00:37:24,940 --> 00:37:26,170
When you two are out there,

852
00:37:26,170 --> 00:37:28,030
you should be patient with each other.

853
00:37:28,030 --> 00:37:29,010
Neither of you should feel

854
00:37:29,010 --> 00:37:31,270
that you are the one who suffers the most.

855
00:37:37,360 --> 00:37:39,320
You'll know
when you meet him in the future.

856
00:37:39,320 --> 00:37:40,510
He's the kind of person

857
00:37:40,510 --> 00:37:42,500
who will never make you
throw a temper tantrum.

858
00:37:42,500 --> 00:37:44,030
When will you bring him back

859
00:37:44,150 --> 00:37:45,280
for me to take a look?

860
00:37:47,960 --> 00:37:49,420
Why are you in such a hurry?

861
00:37:49,840 --> 00:37:50,970
I'm not rushing you.

862
00:37:51,980 --> 00:37:53,000
Whether you rush it

863
00:37:53,000 --> 00:37:53,920
or take your time,

864
00:37:53,920 --> 00:37:55,780
your life is yours to live anyway.

865
00:37:57,710 --> 00:37:58,630
I'm just

866
00:38:00,550 --> 00:38:01,810
looking forward to it.

867
00:38:07,630 --> 00:38:09,400
Zhuang Zhuang, Madam Zhuang!

868
00:38:09,800 --> 00:38:11,800
I'm here to wish you a Happy New Year!

869
00:38:18,350 --> 00:38:19,710
Why bother doing this?

870
00:38:20,070 --> 00:38:21,270
It's what I should do.

871
00:38:21,420 --> 00:38:22,280
Here, Mrs. Qin.

872
00:38:23,480 --> 00:38:25,210
Little Zhuang Zhuang, come on.

873
00:38:26,800 --> 00:38:27,730
No need for that.

874
00:38:27,980 --> 00:38:30,150
-What are you doing, Qin?
-Is this a dessert from Beijing?

875
00:38:30,150 --> 00:38:31,130
Let me try it.

876
00:38:31,420 --> 00:38:32,030
Come on.

877
00:38:32,110 --> 00:38:33,170
What are you doing?

878
00:38:33,420 --> 00:38:34,150
Mom, look at her.

879
00:38:34,150 --> 00:38:35,550
She won't even let me eat.

880
00:38:37,210 --> 00:38:38,170
If Zhuang Zhuang won't let you eat,

881
00:38:38,170 --> 00:38:39,300
then just don't eat.

882
00:38:39,840 --> 00:38:41,230
Listen to Zhuang Zhuang.

883
00:38:41,230 --> 00:38:42,490
Right, Zhuang Zhuang?

884
00:38:44,400 --> 00:38:46,690
Shunyin likes you so much.

885
00:38:47,050 --> 00:38:48,540
He told his dad and me.

886
00:38:48,610 --> 00:38:49,410
He said, "Mom,

887
00:38:49,630 --> 00:38:52,050
I even wish I could pluck the stars
from the sky

888
00:38:52,050 --> 00:38:53,850
and give them to Zhuang Zhuang."

889
00:38:54,690 --> 00:38:55,210
Right?

890
00:38:56,400 --> 00:38:58,800
His dad and I like you, too.

891
00:38:58,800 --> 00:39:00,130
Look how pretty you are.

892
00:39:00,900 --> 00:39:01,900
You look exactly like your mom

893
00:39:01,900 --> 00:39:02,570
when she was young.

894
00:39:02,570 --> 00:39:03,150
Right?

895
00:39:05,670 --> 00:39:06,550
Honestly,

896
00:39:06,630 --> 00:39:07,900
his dad and I

897
00:39:08,030 --> 00:39:09,300
have long seen you

898
00:39:09,320 --> 00:39:10,720
as our daughter-in-law.

899
00:39:12,880 --> 00:39:14,170
Still pouting?

900
00:39:14,920 --> 00:39:16,250
Zhuang Zhuang, tell me.

901
00:39:16,440 --> 00:39:18,460
Is it that his dad and I didn't do well?

902
00:39:18,460 --> 00:39:19,880
Or is it Shunyin's problem?

903
00:39:19,880 --> 00:39:20,630
Tell us,

904
00:39:20,730 --> 00:39:21,940
and we'll change. Is that okay?

905
00:39:21,940 --> 00:39:22,840
Yes, I'll change.

906
00:39:22,840 --> 00:39:23,320
Qin...

907
00:39:23,360 --> 00:39:23,890
Mrs. Qin.

908
00:39:25,110 --> 00:39:26,460
Mrs. Qin, you and your husband

909
00:39:26,460 --> 00:39:27,670
really helped me a lot.

910
00:39:27,670 --> 00:39:28,630
I really appreciate it.

911
00:39:28,630 --> 00:39:29,130
Actually,

912
00:39:29,130 --> 00:39:31,380
I should've been the one
going to visit you for the New Year.

913
00:39:31,380 --> 00:39:32,570
It's New Year's Eve.

914
00:39:32,590 --> 00:39:34,520
Everyone's in good spirits today.

915
00:39:34,530 --> 00:39:36,760
There's something I really shouldn't say.

916
00:39:36,760 --> 00:39:37,210
Why...

917
00:39:37,400 --> 00:39:39,260
Why are we
bringing this up again?

918
00:39:39,630 --> 00:39:41,900
Didn't we make a fuss
about this last year?

919
00:39:41,900 --> 00:39:42,570
When

920
00:39:42,570 --> 00:39:43,800
will this ever end?

921
00:39:44,530 --> 00:39:45,980
You're absolutely right.

922
00:39:45,980 --> 00:39:47,740
You young people are

923
00:39:47,940 --> 00:39:49,590
together one day, breaking up the next,

924
00:39:49,590 --> 00:39:50,790
always making a fuss.

925
00:39:50,800 --> 00:39:51,860
Wouldn't that be great if you two

926
00:39:51,860 --> 00:39:53,260
just be together nicely?

927
00:39:53,610 --> 00:39:55,420
Actually, let me be honest with you.

928
00:39:55,420 --> 00:39:57,090
Our colleagues, friends,

929
00:39:57,090 --> 00:39:57,890
and relatives

930
00:39:58,010 --> 00:40:00,480
all know you two are
going to register for marriage.

931
00:40:00,480 --> 00:40:02,320
His father and I are even preparing

932
00:40:02,320 --> 00:40:04,080
to organize your wedding.

933
00:40:04,170 --> 00:40:05,670
Why are you throwing a tantrum

934
00:40:05,670 --> 00:40:06,550
and wanting to break up?

935
00:40:06,550 --> 00:40:07,530
You can't break up.

936
00:40:07,530 --> 00:40:08,350
If you do...

937
00:40:08,800 --> 00:40:10,130
If you break up, I'll...

938
00:40:10,260 --> 00:40:12,560
I'll be so embarrassed.

939
00:40:12,710 --> 00:40:15,600
Qin, that's in the past.

940
00:40:16,010 --> 00:40:17,210
Why bring it up again?

941
00:40:17,610 --> 00:40:18,890
Yeah, Mrs. Qin.

942
00:40:19,090 --> 00:40:21,590
And what do you mean
by "register for marriage"?

943
00:40:21,590 --> 00:40:23,200
I never agreed to that.

944
00:40:23,320 --> 00:40:23,860
Besides, we were

945
00:40:23,860 --> 00:40:25,520
never even in a relationship.

946
00:40:25,550 --> 00:40:26,510
What do you mean by breaking up

947
00:40:26,510 --> 00:40:27,500
and getting back together?

948
00:40:27,500 --> 00:40:28,230
And those...

949
00:40:28,800 --> 00:40:30,400
Those rumors among the relatives,

950
00:40:30,400 --> 00:40:31,660
didn't your family...

951
00:40:33,210 --> 00:40:33,960
Didn't your family

952
00:40:33,960 --> 00:40:35,460
spread them yourselves, Mrs. Qin?

953
00:40:35,460 --> 00:40:36,190
I hope you

954
00:40:36,190 --> 00:40:37,000
won't use such words

955
00:40:37,000 --> 00:40:38,800
to guilt-trip us anymore, okay?

956
00:40:39,110 --> 00:40:40,240
That's a bit harsh.

957
00:40:40,650 --> 00:40:42,710
How would we dare guilt-trip you?

958
00:40:45,480 --> 00:40:46,540
Then let me ask you.

959
00:40:46,960 --> 00:40:47,840
Tell me,

960
00:40:48,500 --> 00:40:50,590
what exactly is wrong with Shunyin?

961
00:40:50,930 --> 00:40:51,480
Qin.

962
00:40:52,550 --> 00:40:53,090
Let's not

963
00:40:53,090 --> 00:40:55,290
interfere in the kids' business, okay?

964
00:40:58,740 --> 00:41:00,510
Let me say something.

965
00:41:01,590 --> 00:41:03,360
Let me guess, Zhuang Zhuang.

966
00:41:03,980 --> 00:41:05,290
You went to Beijing

967
00:41:05,610 --> 00:41:07,270
and broadened your horizons,

968
00:41:07,420 --> 00:41:08,950
so you look down on Shunyin.

969
00:41:09,510 --> 00:41:10,310
Is that right?

970
00:41:10,780 --> 00:41:11,640
Let me tell you.

971
00:41:11,670 --> 00:41:12,470
In this world,

972
00:41:12,690 --> 00:41:14,070
Shunyin is the man

973
00:41:14,110 --> 00:41:15,240
who treats you best.

974
00:41:15,920 --> 00:41:16,940
Plus, your parents and I are

975
00:41:16,940 --> 00:41:18,260
such good friends.

976
00:41:18,440 --> 00:41:20,000
Really, you can't dump him.

977
00:41:20,000 --> 00:41:20,920
You really can't.

978
00:41:20,920 --> 00:41:22,610
You can't shake off this responsibility.

979
00:41:22,610 --> 00:41:23,980
If you do, you...

980
00:41:24,070 --> 00:41:25,470
I... I'm not a liability.

981
00:41:26,940 --> 00:41:28,000
I'm a super glue!

982
00:41:28,070 --> 00:41:28,760
I'll stick to her

983
00:41:28,760 --> 00:41:29,690
and peel off a layer of her skin.

984
00:41:29,690 --> 00:41:30,340
You know?

985
00:41:31,070 --> 00:41:31,650
Kang.

986
00:41:33,280 --> 00:41:34,380
What are you saying?

987
00:41:34,380 --> 00:41:34,860
I...

988
00:41:36,130 --> 00:41:36,900
Are you

989
00:41:37,010 --> 00:41:38,500
trying to harm our Zhuang Zhuang?

990
00:41:38,500 --> 00:41:39,420
No, no, Mom.

991
00:41:39,500 --> 00:41:40,570
No, well...

992
00:41:41,260 --> 00:41:41,690
Mrs. Zhuang,

993
00:41:41,690 --> 00:41:42,340
I mean,

994
00:41:42,500 --> 00:41:43,980
I would tear off a layer of my own skin.

995
00:41:43,980 --> 00:41:45,130
You just have to push me, don't you?

996
00:41:45,130 --> 00:41:45,460
No.

997
00:41:45,530 --> 00:41:46,980
How am I pushing you?

998
00:41:48,860 --> 00:41:49,320
Fine.

999
00:41:50,110 --> 00:41:50,550
Then let's just

1000
00:41:50,550 --> 00:41:51,750
talk this over today.

1001
00:41:53,980 --> 00:41:55,070
Mrs. Qin, honestly,

1002
00:41:55,070 --> 00:41:56,920
I didn't want to fall out
with anyone today.

1003
00:41:56,920 --> 00:41:59,120
But if you insist on acting like this...

1004
00:42:00,590 --> 00:42:02,520
Are you going to say it, or should I?

1005
00:42:03,980 --> 00:42:04,670
I... I...

1006
00:42:05,550 --> 00:42:07,070
I'll say it.

1007
00:42:07,090 --> 00:42:09,050
I... I love you very much.

1008
00:42:11,480 --> 00:42:11,920
Fine.

1009
00:42:13,720 --> 00:42:14,340
Mrs. Qin.

1010
00:42:14,820 --> 00:42:16,840
Kang Shunyin once went to Beijing
to find me

1011
00:42:16,840 --> 00:42:17,780
and turned my place

1012
00:42:17,780 --> 00:42:18,880
upside down.

1013
00:42:19,130 --> 00:42:20,130
He also stalked me

1014
00:42:20,510 --> 00:42:21,380
and even hit my friend

1015
00:42:21,380 --> 00:42:22,380
with a motorbike.

1016
00:42:23,980 --> 00:42:25,180
When did this happen?

1017
00:42:25,230 --> 00:42:26,010
Who did he hit?

1018
00:42:26,010 --> 00:42:26,780
Was it serious?

1019
00:42:26,780 --> 00:42:27,320
Wait, well...

1020
00:42:27,320 --> 00:42:28,550
Why didn't you tell us?

1021
00:42:28,550 --> 00:42:29,810
Zhuang Zhuang, you...

1022
00:42:29,840 --> 00:42:30,610
Don't talk nonsense.

1023
00:42:30,610 --> 00:42:32,110
I didn't hit anyone. If I did,

1024
00:42:32,110 --> 00:42:33,840
I'd have been... arrested long ago.

1025
00:42:33,840 --> 00:42:34,980
Then come to the police station with me.

1026
00:42:34,980 --> 00:42:36,420
Zhuang Zhuang, why talk about going

1027
00:42:36,420 --> 00:42:38,420
to the police station during the New Year?

1028
00:42:38,420 --> 00:42:39,380
Even now, you...

1029
00:42:39,650 --> 00:42:40,500
You're still defending that man.

1030
00:42:40,500 --> 00:42:42,430
I told you I did catch you cheating.

1031
00:42:42,550 --> 00:42:43,110
Don't you dare...

1032
00:42:43,110 --> 00:42:44,110
What are you talking about?

1033
00:42:44,110 --> 00:42:45,040
What? Cheating?

1034
00:42:45,110 --> 00:42:46,690
Get out. Both of you, get out.

1035
00:42:46,690 --> 00:42:47,230
No, I didn't...

1036
00:42:47,230 --> 00:42:47,880
How dare you make

1037
00:42:47,880 --> 00:42:48,570
false accusations here?

1038
00:42:48,570 --> 00:42:49,070
No, well...

1039
00:42:49,070 --> 00:42:51,030
Zhuang Zhuang already rejected you
a long time ago.

1040
00:42:51,030 --> 00:42:52,410
Who she is with now is

1041
00:42:53,010 --> 00:42:54,630
none of your business!
